      <!-- Section 7: Tracking Performance -->
      <section id="tracking-performance" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>Tracking Your Google AI Overview Performance</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>Measuring AI Overview performance requires a combination of manual SERP monitoring and third-party tooling, as Google does not yet provide dedicated AI Overview reporting in Search Console.</strong>
        </p>

        <h3>Manual SERP Monitoring</h3>
        <p>
          The most direct method: identify your target queries, run them regularly in Google Search (using incognito or a tool that removes personalisation),
          and record whether an AI Overview appears and whether your site is cited. For a focused query set of 20 to 50 terms, manual monitoring
          is feasible on a weekly basis. Document both the trigger rate (does an Overview appear?) and the citation rate (is your site included?).
        </p>

        <h3>Third-Party Rank Tracking Tools</h3>
        <p>
          Several established rank-tracking platforms have added AI Overview detection to their feature sets. SE Ranking, Semrush, and Ahrefs
          each offer varying levels of AI Overview visibility reporting as of mid-2026. These tools automate monitoring across larger query sets
          and provide trend data over time, which is essential for measuring the impact of optimisation changes.
        </p>

        <h3>Traffic and Referral Analysis</h3>
        <p>
          If your pages are cited in AI Overviews with clickable source links, you should see referral traffic from Google search reflected
          in your analytics. While it is difficult to isolate AI Overview clicks from general organic clicks in most analytics setups,
          significant unexplained shifts in click-through rates for specific queries can be correlated with AI Overview appearance
          or citation changes for those terms.
        </p>

        <h3>Connecting to the Broader GEO Picture</h3>
        <p>
          Google AI Overview performance is one dimension of a broader <a href="/ai-brand-visibility/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">AI brand visibility</a> measurement
          programme. A complete picture requires tracking citation across all major AI platforms — not only Google AI Overviews — since
          different platforms serve different user segments and query intents.
          Our <a href="/geo-services/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO services</a> include
          cross-platform citation monitoring as a core component.
        </p>
